1. Ratnici su bili opremljeni *oružjem* različitog kalibra. (The warriors were equipped with *weapons* of various calibers.)
2. Policija je uhapsila čoveka sa ilegalnim *oružjem*. (*Weapons*) (The police arrested a man with illegal *weapons*.)
3. *Oružjem* se ne sme rukovati ukoliko niste obučeni za to. (You should not handle *weapons* if you are not trained to do so.)
4. U zemljama u kojima je nošenje *oružja* dozvoljeno, ljudi često nose pištolje sa sobom. (In countries where carrying *weapons* is allowed, people often carry guns with them.)
5. Naoružani razbojnici su opljačkali banku i pobegli. (Armed robbers *with weapons* robbed the bank and fled.)
6. Poginuli vojnik je bio hrabar borac koji je učestvovao u mnogim bitkama i naučio da rukuje različitim vrstama *oružja*. (The deceased soldier was a brave fighter who participated in many battles and learned to handle different types of *weapons*.)
7. Vlada je donela odluku o smanjenju budžeta za *oružje*. (The government has decided to reduce the budget for *weapons*.)
8. Prema međunarodnom pravu, upotreba *oružja* zabranjena je u određenim situacijama. (According to international law, the use of *weapons* is prohibited in certain situations.)
9. Kriminalci su se predali nakon što su videli da policija ima *oružje*. (The criminals surrendered after they saw that the police had *weapons*.)
10. Vojska je obučena da koristi *oružje* u različitim uslovima, uključujući i nepovoljne vremenske prilike. (The army is trained to use *weapons* in different conditions, including unfavorable weather conditions.)